.ident "@(#)drf:hcomp/drf_mount	1.3"
.related drf_help
.title Help: Mount File Systems
ABOUT THIS OPTION
Select this option to mount the hard disk file systems
under /mnt. For example, the root file (/)system on the 
hard disk is mounted as /mnt and, if /usr is a separate
file system on the hard disk, it is mounted as /mnt/usr. 
Only /, /usr, /home, /stand  and /var file systems on
the hard disk are be mounted.

EXITING HELP
Press 'ESC' to return to the Emergency Recovery Menu.
Press 'F1' for more help.
